  "course_description": "This course explores how to make quantitative research and technical knowledge accessible beyond specialized fields. Writing is treated as a tool for shaping present thinking, not just reporting past work. Students will practice genres such as research translations, code notebooks, reports, presentations, and posters, learning to communicate methodological choices to both expert and general audiences. The course also examines how communication reflects disciplinary norms and how data informs knowledge-making. It emphasizes transparency and reproducibility as key practices in ethical research and prepares students to communicate data effectively.",
